   <abstract lang="eng">This report describes the background, numerical methods, and results of a theoretical and experimental study of the pressure waves generated by a sudden release of energy along a straight line. Although this work has no direct relationship to the atmospheric sciences, it was carried out as the first step in a numerical study of the pressure wave from a lightning discharge, which approximates a line source.</abstract>
